
FAMILY CONNECTIONS 2.4.1


I. Installation
----------------

  1. Upload the entire contents of FCMS_2.4.1.zip to your web host.

  2. Run the online installation script by visiting your website.

        If you installed Family Connections in a directory called
        fcms/ and your domain is yourdomain.com, then you would 
        type in the url http://www.yourdomain.com/fcms/ into your
        browser.

  4. It is recommended that you delete the install.php file after installation.




II. Upgrading from 2.4 to 2.4.1
--------------------------------
  ** DO NOT DELETE THE FOLLOWING FILE **
    inc/config_inc.php

  ** DO NOT TOUCH ANY FILES IN THE FOLLOWING DIRECTORIES **
    gallery/avatar/
    gallery/documents/
    gallery/photos/memberX/
    gallery/upimages/

  FCMS 2.5 includes a new feature where you can do automatic upgrades.  If you are
  upgrading from version 2.4 or later you can make use of this new feature and do
  a semi-automatic upgrade.  Subsequent versions will be fully automatic.

  1. It is recommended that you backup your entire site, including your
     MySQL database before upgrading.

  2. Login as the administrator and visit the upgrade section (keep this window open).

  3. Upload the entire contents of FCMS_2.4.1.zip to your web host 
     (Overwriting any previous files other than the above mentioned files/directories).

  4. Login as the administrator and visit the upgrade section and run the
     upgrade script.

  4. Delete the following files:

       inc/util_inc.php

  5. Go back to your browser (from step 2) and refresh the page.  You will probably get
     a few errors at the top.  Click the 'Automatic Upgrade' button.

  5. Delete the install.php file from your web host (if it still exists).



